'''Ibrahim Bayesh Kamil Al-Kaabawi''' ({{langx|ar|إبرَاهِيْم بَايَش كَامِل الْكَعْبَاوِيّ}}; born 1 May 2000) is an Iraqi professional footballer who plays [[Al Dhafra FC|Al-Dhafra]] as a [[midfielder]]<ref>{{Kooora|127285}}</ref><ref>[http://www.worldfootball.com/p/143175/iraq/Ibrahim%20Bayesh Ibrahim Bayesh] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180812021357/http://www.worldfootball.com/p/143175/iraq/Ibrahim%20Bayesh |date=2018-08-12 }} at WorldFootball.net</ref> for [[UAE Pro League]] club [[Al Dhafra FC|Al-Dhafra]] and the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

== Club career ==

=== Early career ===
Bayesh joined Naft Al Wasat from Zakho in February 2017, to play the second half of the 16-17 season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Al Husseini |first1=Maytham |title=بايش يقترب من تمثيل نفط الوسط |date=10 July 2019 |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=562439 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref>

=== Al Zawra'a ===
Following his stint with Naft Al Wasat, Bayesh was close to joining Tunisian side [[Étoile Sportive du Sahel]],<ref>{{cite web |last1=Al-Habasi |first1=Ahmed |title=بعد تعثر مفاوضاته مع النجم ..العراقي ابراهيم بايش يلتحق بالقوة الجوية |url=https://www.jawharafm.net/ar/article/%D8%A8%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%AB%D8%B1-%D9%85%D9%81%D8%A7%D9%88%D8%B6%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%AC%D9%85-..%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B4-%D9%8A%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%AD%D9%82-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9/96/120145 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref> however, talks broke down at the contract stage, and he signed for Baghdad side Al-Zawra'a.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Al Husseini |first1=Maytham |title=إبراهيم بايش ينتقل إلى الزوراء |date=9 July 2019 |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=616738 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref> Bayesh only spent one season with Al-Zawra'a, where the team won the [[2017–18 Iraqi Premier League|17-18]] league title. Bayesh's contract was terminated in June, due to disputes with the club, where the player missed two weeks on training unauthorized.<ref>{{cite web |title=رسمياً.. الزوراء يفسخ تعاقده مع ابراهيم بايش |url=https://www.alsumaria.tv/Entertainment-News/240337/sports/%D8%B1%D8%B3%D9%85%D9%8A%D8%A7%D9%8B-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B2%D9%88%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%A1-%D9%8A%D9%81%D8%B3%D8%AE-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%B9-%D8%A7%D8%A8%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%8A%D9%85-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%8A%D8%B4 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref>

=== Al Quwa Al Jawiya ===

The following season, Bayesh joined Al-Zawra'a rivals [[Al Quwa Al Jawiya]], In October 2018, Bayesh scored the second goal in the final of [[2018 AFC Cup]], which his team won.<ref>{{cite web |title=ثلاثية تاريخية للعراق.. القوة الجوية يتوّج بكأس الاتحاد الآسيوي |url=https://www.aljazeera.net/sport/2018/10/27/%D8%AB%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AB%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8A%D8%AE%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D9%84%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D9%88%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%A9 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref>

== International career ==

Bayesh was called up to the [[23rd Arabian Gulf Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |title=خليجي 23: إعلان قائمة المنتخب العراقي |url=https://www.beinsports.com/ar-mena/%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85/%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A3%D8%AE%D8%A8%D8%A7%D8%B1/%D8%AE%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AC%D9%8A-23-%D8%A5%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%86-%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A6%D9%85%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%86 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref> in which Iraq were knocked out in the Semi Final, but the player was on the bench throughout the entire tournament.

Bayesh was called up to the [[24th Arabian Gulf Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |title=جلال حسن حارس مرمى العراق:طموحنا التتويج باللقب |url=https://al-sharq.com/article/24/11/2019/%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%84-%D8%AD%D8%B3%D9%86-%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B1%D8%B3-%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%85%D9%89-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82%D8%B7%D9%85%D9%88%D8%AD%D9%86%D8%A7-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AA%D8%AA%D9%88%D9%8A%D8%AC-%D8%A8%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A8 |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref> in which Iraq lost in the Semi Final against Bahrain on penalties, with Bayesh scoring in the shootout.<ref>{{cite web |title=البحرين تعبر العراق إلى نهائي كأس الخليج |url=https://www.skynewsarabia.com/sport/1303070-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A8%D8%AD%D8%B1%D9%8A%D9%86-%D8%AA%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%B1-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%82-%D9%86%D9%87%D8%A7%D9%8A%D9%94%D9%8A-%D9%83%D8%A7%D9%94%D8%B3-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AE%D9%84%D9%8A%D8%AC |access-date=12 December 2024}}</ref>

